  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this pilot program is to develop and evaluate a new treatment program for
      depression in Parkinson's disease (PD). The treatment uses Cognitive Behavior Therapy(CBT)to
      teach patients how to become more aware of their thoughts and feelings and to change thinking
      patterns and behaviors that may be related to depressive symptoms. This is the first time
      that this treatment has been used in a group setting for depression in PD.

      Target population is patients in the Movement Disorders Clinic at Oregon Health &amp; Science
      University who have Parkinson's disease and mild to moderate depression.
    </textblock>
